1
00:00:03,204 --> 00:00:05,070
    Order, order everypony!

2
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:06,738
        I hereby call to
       order this meeting

3
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:08,840
 of the Rainbow Dash Fan Club!

4
00:00:12,613 --> 00:00:13,745
    First order of business:

5
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:15,481
    Let's celebrate the one
    and only Rainbow Dash!

6
00:00:15,583 --> 00:00:16,949
    Yay! She's amazing. Now
    if there's nothing else,

7
00:00:17,051 --> 00:00:18,718
 that concludes this meeting of
 the Rainbow Dash Fan Club.

8
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:19,986
   Thank you all for coming.
    Any questions?

9
00:00:23,257 --> 00:00:24,023
              Huh?

10
00:00:24,825 --> 00:00:25,857
       Meeting adjourned!

11
00:00:32,199 --> 00:00:34,465
   I'd like to call to order
   the first ever meeting

12
00:00:34,568 --> 00:00:36,802
    of the newest and
     most exciting club...

13
00:00:36,904 --> 00:00:39,972
  of which I am the president,
  founding, and only member...

14
00:00:40,174 --> 00:00:41,974
     The Washouts Fan Club!

15
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:27,018
    Oh, hey Scootaloo, I was
     just in the neighbor--

16
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,487
        Oh, what's this?

17
00:01:29,757 --> 00:01:32,090
Did I interrupt your
fan club meeting?

18
00:01:32,292 --> 00:01:34,960
        Hey! What are
        you doing here?

19
00:01:35,162 --> 00:01:37,296
I could ask you
the same question!

20
00:01:37,898 --> 00:01:41,267
   Oh uh, you know... stuff.

21
00:01:41,869 --> 00:01:44,269
   Definitely not starting a
   new fan club or anything...

22
00:01:44,571 --> 00:01:46,338
HA! It's no use
pretending.

23
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:48,840
I heard everything
when I was outside eavesdropping

24
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:50,776
like I do for
every meeting!

25
00:01:50,978 --> 00:01:52,544
        You eavesdrop on
         every meeting?

26
00:01:52,646 --> 00:01:54,079
        That's... weird.

27
00:01:54,681 --> 00:01:57,816
Well, sure it sounds weird
when you say it out loud.

28
00:01:57,918 --> 00:02:00,285
And I probably shouldn't because
eavesdropping is wrong,

29
00:02:00,387 --> 00:02:01,286
          but still...

30
00:02:01,388 --> 00:02:03,689
Why are you starting
a new fan club?

31
00:02:04,091 --> 00:02:07,392
   I just think maybe it's
   time for me to explore...

32
00:02:07,494 --> 00:02:08,994
        other fan clubs.

33
00:02:14,935 --> 00:02:17,502
   What is a "The Washouts?"

34
00:02:17,604 --> 00:02:21,473
Only the newest and greatest and
ONLY stunt troupe in Equestria!

35
00:02:21,675 --> 00:02:22,841
         Stunt troupe?

36
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:25,076
     How can I explain it?
     Like the Wonderbolts,

37
00:02:25,178 --> 00:02:28,847
     just TWENTY BAJILLION
     PERCENT COOLER.

38
00:02:29,449 --> 00:02:31,049
       Twenty bajillion!?

39
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:34,119
  They do all sorts of extreme
stunts that focus on daredevilry

40
00:02:34,221 --> 00:02:36,254
     and sheer guts, rather
    than boring old

41
00:02:36,356 --> 00:02:38,123
   flight-and-formation junk.

42
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:41,560
       Boring old flight
      and formation junk!?

43
00:02:41,762 --> 00:02:43,662
Are you just repeating
everything I say?

44
00:02:43,864 --> 00:02:45,497
     Only because my brain
    feels like it's strapped

45
00:02:45,599 --> 00:02:47,432
    to one of those rockets
    about to explode.

46
00:02:47,634 --> 00:02:48,634
So you do
 get it!

47
00:02:49,036 --> 00:02:50,902
Aren't they awesome?

48
00:02:54,241 --> 00:02:56,942
      Can you believe she
      actually said that?

49
00:02:57,244 --> 00:03:01,446
 Pfft. Well, yeah, eavesdropping on
 every meeting is kinda weird.

50
00:03:01,748 --> 00:03:05,784
 I mean she basically said that
  the Wonderbolts aren't cool!

51
00:03:05,886 --> 00:03:09,288
 And.. and it kinda sounded like she
didn't think I was cool either.

52
00:03:09,490 --> 00:03:12,824
              But pah! We all
              know that's crazy.

53
00:03:12,926 --> 00:03:14,926
     I mean, I'm definitely
      not worried

54
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:17,362
      about her looking up
       to somepony else.

55
00:03:17,464 --> 00:03:18,563
             Heh. Nope.

56
00:03:18,665 --> 00:03:19,364
              Not.

57
00:03:19,466 --> 00:03:20,132
              At.

58
00:03:20,234 --> 00:03:21,200
              ALL.

59
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:23,435
Well, I'd understand
if you were.

60
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:26,104
It'd be like if Apple Bloom
started lovin' bananas

61
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:27,172
more than apples!

62
00:03:27,274 --> 00:03:28,874
Hahaha!

63
00:03:29,176 --> 00:03:30,909
Y'all tell me if that
ever happens, you hear?

64
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:35,046
  But what could the Washouts
  possibly have that I don't?

65
00:03:35,148 --> 00:03:36,381
         Why don't you find out?

66
00:03:37,985 --> 00:03:41,419
    They're doing a show in
    Ponyville this weekend!?

67
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:48,827
Wow... they do look pretty
amazing...ly unamazing. Heh.

68
00:03:48,929 --> 00:03:51,930
Trying so hard to look
amazing, is what I mean.

69
00:03:52,532 --> 00:03:55,099
            NICE SAVE, TWILIGHT!

70
00:04:04,144 --> 00:04:07,545
[groan] I knew we should have
lined up last night.

71
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:15,120
I'm sorry for making us late.
Who would have guessed

72
00:04:15,222 --> 00:04:17,956
X-TREME CHOCOLATE AIR SHOW
CUPCAKES would take an...

73
00:04:18,058 --> 00:04:20,558
x-tremely long time to bake?

74
00:04:25,332 --> 00:04:28,967
      Look at this! It's a
      total Wonderbolts rip-off!

75
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,836
   What do you mean? The show
    hasn't even started yet!

76
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,972
     Yeah, but look at what
       we're sitting on.

77
00:04:34,975 --> 00:04:36,441
                   <i>Hello!</i>

78
00:04:36,543 --> 00:04:38,877
            The Wonderbolts
             have bleachers too.

79
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:41,988
         We practically invented
          sitting on bleachers.

80
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:43,048
                          Ugh!

81
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:48,453
   And look at that! Popcorn
   and cotton candy? RIP-OFF!

82
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:52,991
             Huh!? Yeah!

83
00:04:53,093 --> 00:04:54,959
     [aggressive announcer]
    <i> This is the time.</i>

84
00:04:55,061 --> 00:04:56,995
      <i> This is the place.</i>

85
00:04:57,197 --> 00:04:59,364
      <i> This is the team...</i>

86
00:04:59,766 --> 00:05:04,102
   <i> THIS IS... THE WASHOUTS!</i>

87
00:05:07,875 --> 00:05:10,075
Eh. Quality confetti
cannon work!

88
00:05:10,877 --> 00:05:11,843
                        Agh!

89
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,416
           Oh, yeah!

90
00:05:21,688 --> 00:05:26,291
    <i> Say it with me now, the</i>
  <i> Washout's official motto...</i>

91
00:05:26,493 --> 00:05:29,828
    "LEAP BEFORE YOU LOOK!"

92
00:05:32,432 --> 00:05:33,131
             Lame.

93
00:05:38,772 --> 00:05:41,540
  <i> Remember ponies, while</i>
  <i> they're amazingly awesome,</i>

94
00:05:41,642 --> 00:05:44,009
    <i> The Washouts are highly</i>
    <i> trained professionals</i>

95
00:05:44,111 --> 00:05:47,312
      <i> with protective</i>
    <i> fireproof flight suits!</i>

96
00:05:47,414 --> 00:05:49,781
   <i> Do not try this at home!</i>

97
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:01,693
             Whoa.

98
00:06:04,597 --> 00:06:06,231
            Come on! Come on!

99
00:06:09,135 --> 00:06:10,469
    She's not gonna make it!

100
00:06:12,505 --> 00:06:13,638
       [collective gasp]

101
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,580
        THAT. WAS. INSANE!

102
00:06:22,682 --> 00:06:24,749
                    WHOO HOO!

103
00:06:24,851 --> 00:06:26,218
          I told you!

104
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,455
             I mean... [ahem] it
            was pretty cool.

105
00:06:30,957 --> 00:06:32,724
      Who are these guys..?

106
00:06:38,865 --> 00:06:41,566
       I can't just go up
       and TALK to them!

107
00:06:41,668 --> 00:06:43,301
   You can if you're with me.

108
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:46,671
 After all, one of the reasons
there's a Rainbow Dash fan club

109
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:49,741
      is because I'm
       fearless. Observe.

110
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:55,680
   Hey!

111
00:06:58,751 --> 00:07:00,351
Uh... so...

112
00:07:00,453 --> 00:07:02,353
as a fellow aerobatic
professional,

113
00:07:02,455 --> 00:07:04,689
I really enjoyed
your show.

114
00:07:04,891 --> 00:07:08,026
 Heh, actually, you might
  recognize me since I'm a...

115
00:07:08,228 --> 00:07:09,962
 "pause for dramatic effect..."

116
00:07:11,064 --> 00:07:12,864
         A Wonderbolt.

117
00:07:15,769 --> 00:07:16,935
                Join the club!

118
00:07:18,571 --> 00:07:20,839
         OK....?

119
00:07:22,141 --> 00:07:24,476
   No, I mean literally join
   the club. We're called

120
00:07:24,578 --> 00:07:26,778
   "The Washouts" because we
  all used to be Wonderbolts

121
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:29,948
     just like you... until
     we "washed out."

122
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:31,950
            No way!

123
00:07:32,352 --> 00:07:33,384
                   Yep. Ah.

124
00:07:33,486 --> 00:07:34,719
     Name's Rolling Thunder.

125
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:37,088
  I got booted out of
  Wonderbolt Academy cause of

126
00:07:37,190 --> 00:07:40,058
   "flagrant disregard for
    hazardous weather." Psh.

127
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:42,360
 If doin' barrel rolls through
 nine-hundred million volts

128
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:44,729
   of electricity in a raging
   thunderstorm is wrong,

129
00:07:44,931 --> 00:07:46,598
 then I don't want to be right.

130
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:48,968
Cool!

131
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:51,403
   Heh. This here's Short Fuse...

132
00:07:51,705 --> 00:07:52,737
       Ah. Nice to meet you.

133
00:07:52,939 --> 00:07:54,005
What's your story?

134
00:07:54,507 --> 00:07:55,540
         ANGER ISSUES!

135
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:57,442
        GET OFF MY BACK!

136
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:00,612
            Uh, OK.

137
00:08:00,914 --> 00:08:03,348
So... who's the leader?

138
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:08,086
  Only the most reckless
  ex-Wonderbolt of all time...

139
00:08:08,188 --> 00:08:15,890
               ♪♪

140
00:08:16,063 --> 00:08:18,329
       [gasp] Lightning Dust!

141
00:08:18,631 --> 00:08:20,398
Rainbow Dash.

142
00:08:21,568 --> 00:08:24,603
         Scootaloo. I'm
         Scootaloo. Hi.

143
00:08:30,243 --> 00:08:31,543
       Lightning Dust...

144
00:08:31,645 --> 00:08:33,645
         I should have known you
         were the brains behind

145
00:08:33,747 --> 00:08:36,081
               a crazy idea like
               the Washouts.

146
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:38,950
               Or should I say
               "lack of brains."

147
00:08:40,020 --> 00:08:42,053
You two really know each other?

148
00:08:42,155 --> 00:08:46,692
  OH MY GOSH THIS IS SO COOL!

149
00:08:46,894 --> 00:08:49,694
Your friend got me kicked
out of the Wonderbolts.

150
00:08:50,096 --> 00:08:53,232
  Oh. That's, uh... less cool.

151
00:08:54,134 --> 00:08:56,936
   And it was the best thing
   that ever happened to me!

152
00:08:57,638 --> 00:08:59,404
Great to see you,
"Wing Pony!"

153
00:08:59,506 --> 00:09:01,673
I heard you're a
full-fledged Bolt now!

154
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,642
Yeah, well,
I'm still--

155
00:09:03,744 --> 00:09:04,543
           Mad at me?

156
00:09:04,945 --> 00:09:06,745
       Look, was it wrong
       of me to endanger

157
00:09:06,847 --> 00:09:08,747
       the lives of your
       friends? Yeah.

158
00:09:08,849 --> 00:09:11,983
But hey, now I only
endanger these knuckleheads!

159
00:09:13,687 --> 00:09:15,454
   Don't call me <i>knucklehead</i>.

160
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:20,826
 Come on, you know you miss me.

161
00:09:20,928 --> 00:09:24,329
   Me and her? We blew
   everypony out of the sky.

162
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:25,964
            Really!?

163
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:30,802
Actually yeah, really. All that
 wind was totally dangerous.

164
00:09:30,904 --> 00:09:32,203
     But we had fun, right?

165
00:09:32,305 --> 00:09:34,673
       Two fastest times
       on the Dizzitron.

166
00:09:34,775 --> 00:09:38,410
 If I remember correctly, I had
  you beat by half a second.

167
00:09:38,612 --> 00:09:42,714
Only because when I went, I
cranked up the dizziness factor!

168
00:09:44,585 --> 00:09:46,417
Well, I'm glad it
all worked out.

169
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:48,587
Your show was
pretty dynamite.

170
00:09:48,889 --> 00:09:50,155
          Wanna know the secret?

171
00:09:50,257 --> 00:09:52,924
    We basically ignore
   everything the Wonderbolts

172
00:09:53,026 --> 00:09:54,826
  ever taught us about safety.

173
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:59,230
Well, we do have safety
rules for a reason.

174
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:00,783
                 Don't listen to
                 her, kid.

175
00:10:00,884 --> 00:10:03,935
All their "rules" were just ways
of keeping their little club

176
00:10:04,037 --> 00:10:06,838
  exclusive so they could
  feel good about themselves.

177
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,907
     It's not about making
     anypony feel bad,

178
00:10:09,009 --> 00:10:11,109
       it's about finding
        the best flyers.

179
00:10:11,211 --> 00:10:12,678
     The best of the best.

180
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:16,948
   I started the Washouts
   because I believe anypony

181
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:18,817
  can be the best of the best.

182
00:10:20,754 --> 00:10:21,820
          You know...

183
00:10:21,922 --> 00:10:24,390
    Rolling Thunder is gonna
      be out for a while...

184
00:10:24,892 --> 00:10:27,492
         Ah! During the finale, I
         caught the ol' hind leg

185
00:10:27,594 --> 00:10:30,830
  in the Crushinator Jaws of
  Smash-a-lot, patent pending.

186
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:34,966
      There's a spot on the team
      if you want to join up.

187
00:10:37,403 --> 00:10:40,605
I appreciate the offer, but
I'm already a Wonderbolt.

188
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:42,374
    I'll do it! Can I do it?

189
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:44,710
Lemme think: no?

190
00:10:45,312 --> 00:10:47,212
            I wasn't asking <i>you</i>.

191
00:10:48,114 --> 00:10:49,414
                Aw, you're cute.

192
00:10:49,516 --> 00:10:51,616
  But technically, you haven't
  "washed out" of the Bolts,

193
00:10:51,718 --> 00:10:53,852
  which is kinda... our thing.

194
00:10:53,954 --> 00:10:56,555
And also... "No!"

195
00:10:56,657 --> 00:10:59,057
Oh! What if I joined and
dropped out super-quick?

196
00:10:59,359 --> 00:11:00,992
       That's it! You're
        coming with me!

197
00:11:01,962 --> 00:11:03,262
      Where are we going?

198
00:11:03,464 --> 00:11:05,964
  To hear what the actual
  Wonderbolts think about you

199
00:11:06,066 --> 00:11:08,901
     joining just to drop
     out for the Washouts.

200
00:11:09,703 --> 00:11:12,003
   Say "hi" to Spitfire for me!

201
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,846
                   Ever seen two
                   simultaneous

202
00:11:21,948 --> 00:11:24,483
            inverse displacement
            rolls before?

203
00:11:24,585 --> 00:11:26,352
Pfft. Woulda been alot
cooler through the

204
00:11:26,453 --> 00:11:29,220
Crushinator Jaws of
Smash-a-lot, patent pending.

205
00:11:30,123 --> 00:11:31,790
                    You... What!?

206
00:11:32,092 --> 00:11:34,526
See, this is what I
was telling you about!

207
00:11:34,931 --> 00:11:35,964
                  I got this.

208
00:11:37,565 --> 00:11:39,798
    You know what happens
   when something goes <i>wrong</i>

209
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:42,167
      with the Crushinator
      Jaws of Smash-a-lot?

210
00:11:42,469 --> 00:11:43,668
            "...Patent pending?"

211
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:46,505
     You end up in a
  full-body-wing-and-hoof cast

212
00:11:46,707 --> 00:11:48,374
   drinkin' through a straw!

213
00:11:49,776 --> 00:11:51,376
  But with enough practice...

214
00:11:51,478 --> 00:11:52,295
                    Practice!?

215
00:11:52,396 --> 00:11:55,613
       Well, la-dee-<i> doodle</i> -da!

216
00:11:55,816 --> 00:11:57,782
Let me give you a
different scenario.

217
00:11:57,984 --> 00:11:59,217
You're probably
saying to yourself,

218
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:01,219
"I'm young, I'm strong.

219
00:12:01,321 --> 00:12:04,756
I'm gonna go out there
and "stunt" some "tricks"

220
00:12:04,858 --> 00:12:07,425
with my new friend,
Lightning Dust.

221
00:12:07,627 --> 00:12:10,595
Well, I'm here to tell
you if you play that game,

222
00:12:10,697 --> 00:12:14,299
you're gonna find out it's
pretty hard to "stunt tricks"

223
00:12:14,401 --> 00:12:19,705
  in a FULL-BODY-WING-AND-HOOF
 CAST DRINKIN' THROUGH A STRAW!

224
00:12:20,207 --> 00:12:21,406
                 I think she
                 gets the point-

225
00:12:21,508 --> 00:12:23,174
       I'M NOT FINISHED!

226
00:12:23,476 --> 00:12:26,611
     Listen, I get it, kid.
     I used to be like you.

227
00:12:26,813 --> 00:12:29,781
     Tellin' myself: "I'm
     gonna touch the sky!"

228
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:30,716
I don't--

229
00:12:30,818 --> 00:12:33,785
     Well,
     WHOOP-DEE-DOODLE-DOO!

230
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:36,421
      You think you got it
      made in the shade?

231
00:12:36,523 --> 00:12:39,024
     Well, things are gonna
     be pretty shady indeed

232
00:12:39,126 --> 00:12:42,193
  when you can't go out in the
    sun cause you're in

233
00:12:42,295 --> 00:12:47,365
 a FULL-BODY-WING-AND-HOOF
 CAST DRINKIN' THROUGH A STRAW!

234
00:12:47,467 --> 00:12:50,569
    DO I MAKE MYSELF CLEAR?

235
00:12:52,339 --> 00:12:54,873
                     Excellent.
                     Have a hat.

236
00:12:57,210 --> 00:13:01,113
Er, sorry. That was a
little... intense.

237
00:13:01,815 --> 00:13:04,149
    I just want to make
    sure you don't get hurt.

238
00:13:04,551 --> 00:13:06,751
    That way you can
    follow in my hoofsteps.

239
00:13:07,053 --> 00:13:08,954
   Everypony's dream, right?

