00:13:09,456 --> 00:13:11,756
               More like "follow
               your wing-flaps."

241
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:12,824
Same difference.

242
00:13:14,394 --> 00:13:16,361
Thanks, "super-
talented flyer,"

243
00:13:16,463 --> 00:13:19,030
for clearing up
what <i>I</i> should do!

244
00:13:19,132 --> 00:13:21,900
Clearing things up is
one of my specialties.

245
00:13:22,002 --> 00:13:24,736
Now come on, let's go rip up
all your Washout posters

246
00:13:24,838 --> 00:13:27,472
into tiny pieces and
throw 'em off a cliff.

247
00:13:31,812 --> 00:13:33,678
   I just thought of a great
    way to raise awareness

248
00:13:33,780 --> 00:13:36,849
  for your original fan club.
  You know, the one about me.

249
00:13:37,851 --> 00:13:40,018
    How about a silent
    auction where every item

250
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,653
       is just a picture
        of yours truly?

251
00:13:41,755 --> 00:13:43,655
 Haha, nahhh, I'm just kidding.

252
00:13:44,257 --> 00:13:46,424
     That makes me seem too
    egotistical, doesn't it?

253
00:13:46,526 --> 00:13:48,359
        OH OH! But maybe
       if they're framed,

254
00:13:48,461 --> 00:13:50,995
   it's like, "Wow, she's so
   humble", you think?

255
00:13:52,999 --> 00:13:53,765
         Scootaloo...?

256
00:13:54,835 --> 00:13:56,134
           Er. Scootaloo?

257
00:13:57,871 --> 00:13:59,170
    Anypony seen Scootaloo?

258
00:14:00,273 --> 00:14:03,241
     My fault, my fault--
     sorry, I... Twilight!

259
00:14:04,711 --> 00:14:07,345
    Sorry, I was just, um...

260
00:14:08,782 --> 00:14:10,982
Please tell me you got that
stuff so you could rip it up

261
00:14:11,084 --> 00:14:12,284
and throw it off a cliff.

262
00:14:12,485 --> 00:14:15,485
  They were doing an autograph
  session before practice..

263
00:14:15,588 --> 00:14:17,922
Seriously? Ugh.

264
00:14:18,224 --> 00:14:19,758
You haven't seen
Scoot, have you?

265
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:21,426
                 Actually...

266
00:14:24,197 --> 00:14:25,797
              I can't believe
            Scootaloo ditched me

267
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:27,498
         to watch them "practice"!

268
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,868
           Why can't she see how
           dangerous they are?

269
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:31,603
That's kind of
the whole draw.

270
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:32,671
It's exciting.

271
00:14:32,772 --> 00:14:35,038
        But it's like the harder
        I try to convince Scoot

272
00:14:35,141 --> 00:14:37,809
          they're dangerous, the
          more she likes them!

273
00:14:38,211 --> 00:14:40,912
You can't control her
actions, only yours.

274
00:14:41,114 --> 00:14:44,082
 Teach her what's safe and what
 isn't, like a good role model,

275
00:14:44,284 --> 00:14:46,317
then hope she makes
the right decisions.

276
00:14:46,519 --> 00:14:48,953
          But what if she
           chooses them over me?

277
00:14:49,055 --> 00:14:50,422
           She's gonna get hurt.

278
00:14:50,924 --> 00:14:53,057
I think I know somepony
else who might get hurt

279
00:14:53,159 --> 00:14:54,192
if that happens.

280
00:14:55,996 --> 00:14:57,128
      Maybe you're right.

281
00:14:57,230 --> 00:14:58,529
    But this isn't about me.

282
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,665
 I'm just worried about Scoot.

283
00:15:04,304 --> 00:15:07,572
Wow, you're really working
hard on this new stunt.

284
00:15:09,175 --> 00:15:13,411
 WHAT KIND OF SORRY EXCUSE FOR
 A TOMATO SANDWICH IS THIS?

285
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:20,551
Sorry Dash, autograph
session's over.

286
00:15:20,653 --> 00:15:22,921
Unless you want to buy
Short Fuse's limited-edition

287
00:15:23,023 --> 00:15:24,489
half-eaten
tomato sandwich.

288
00:15:24,691 --> 00:15:28,694
        I'M NOT SIGNING
       THAT ABOMINATION!

289
00:15:29,296 --> 00:15:31,196
            You haven't seen
            Scootaloo, have you?

290
00:15:31,298 --> 00:15:35,500
Oh! Isn't she that pony
that used to respect you?

291
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,704
     I'd appreciate you
     helping me find her...

292
00:15:39,806 --> 00:15:42,707
 so I can apologize for trying
 to make her quit liking you.

293
00:15:43,209 --> 00:15:47,712
  [mean laugh] Oh, I'm pretty
   sure she still likes us.

294
00:15:57,223 --> 00:15:59,490
       Lightning Dust, I
      know we go way back,

295
00:15:59,692 --> 00:16:01,692
        but I can't let
         her do this!

296
00:16:01,894 --> 00:16:04,395
     I don't need <i>you</i>
      standing up for me.

297
00:16:04,497 --> 00:16:08,633
Obviously you do, because you
can't see how dangerous this is.

298
00:16:08,735 --> 00:16:11,235
      Do you not remember
      what Spitfire said?

299
00:16:11,337 --> 00:16:12,971
       Ugh, lemme guess,

300
00:16:13,473 --> 00:16:16,040
   "You'll be in a
  full-body-wing-and-hoof cast

301
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:18,777
   drinkin' through a straw!"

302
00:16:19,079 --> 00:16:20,945
     That doesn't even
      sound like Spitfire.

303
00:16:22,515 --> 00:16:23,981
                   That's it,
                  we're leaving!

304
00:16:25,218 --> 00:16:26,651
Just because I
look up to you

305
00:16:26,853 --> 00:16:28,820
doesn't mean I
have to BE you!

306
00:16:29,322 --> 00:16:32,590
 But based on your definition
 of what makes somepony great,

307
00:16:32,692 --> 00:16:36,160
I have bad news: I'll NEVER
be the "best of the best",

308
00:16:36,262 --> 00:16:40,632
or a Wonderbolt
because I. CAN'T. FLY.

309
00:16:41,434 --> 00:16:43,234
Is that what you wanted to hear?

310
00:16:44,737 --> 00:16:46,404
But not being able
to fly doesn't mean

311
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:48,406
I can't do
something awesome,

312
00:16:48,508 --> 00:16:52,043
like strapping my scooter to a
multi-stage liquid-fuel rocket

313
00:16:52,145 --> 00:16:54,178
and jumping twenty
two wagons lined up

314
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:56,147
in front of a
roaring crowd!

315
00:16:56,749 --> 00:16:58,182
   That was awfully specific.

316
00:16:58,584 --> 00:17:01,186
That's cause it's what she'll
be doing in the show tonight.

317
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:04,489
Half-off for Princesses!
Bring your friends.

318
00:17:05,291 --> 00:17:08,593
Scootaloo, are you sure that's
what you really want to do?

319
00:17:08,995 --> 00:17:10,261
          Absolutely.

320
00:17:10,863 --> 00:17:13,932
And there's <i>nothing</i>
you can do to stop me!

321
00:17:14,234 --> 00:17:16,000
            You're right. You're
            your own foal

322
00:17:16,102 --> 00:17:18,203
            and you have to make
            your own decisions.

323
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:21,139
Good. Because I already have.

324
00:17:24,477 --> 00:17:25,376
                             Oh.

325
00:17:28,148 --> 00:17:30,048
      I'm sorry for making
      us late again.

326
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:31,049
     Who would have guessed

327
00:17:31,151 --> 00:17:33,017
   Scootaloo's Super-
    Difficult-Stunt-Special

328
00:17:33,119 --> 00:17:36,220
   Cupcakes would have been
  so super-difficult to bake?

329
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:43,196
    Whoo wee, looks like all
     of Ponyville's here...

330
00:17:44,898 --> 00:17:46,364
    except for Rainbow Dash.

331
00:17:47,583 --> 00:17:49,799
      [Announcer]<i> And here to</i>
     <i> introduce the most</i>
    <i> dangerous stunt</i>

332
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:54,672
  <i> we've ever performed, it's</i>
   <i> your fearless captain...</i>

333
00:17:54,774 --> 00:17:58,576
   <i> La La La Lightning Dust!</i>

334
00:18:04,484 --> 00:18:08,119
  In just a moment, the newest
  member of the Washouts

335
00:18:08,221 --> 00:18:12,857
  will be ROCKET-SLEDDING down
 that hill, up that ramp,

336
00:18:13,059 --> 00:18:17,862
and over all twenty-two wagons,
 to land on the other side...

337
00:18:17,964 --> 00:18:19,298
        in one piece...

338
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,466
       ..heh ...if she's lucky.

339
00:18:21,568 --> 00:18:26,570
    Put your hooves together
    for HALF-PINT DYNAMITE!

340
00:18:28,942 --> 00:18:30,675
           Whoo yeah!

341
00:18:36,149 --> 00:18:37,099
        Lightning Dust?

342
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:40,150
 I have to tell you, I actually
started Equestria's first

343
00:18:40,253 --> 00:18:42,520
      Washouts Fan Club...
       as far as I know.

344
00:18:42,622 --> 00:18:45,923
So this is a real honor, ma'am.
Umm, do we call you ma'am?

345
00:18:46,025 --> 00:18:49,227
  You land this jump, you can
  call me whatever you want.

346
00:18:52,565 --> 00:18:54,933
      Wow, that sure is...

347
00:18:55,135 --> 00:18:57,035
        Dangerous? Nahh.

348
00:18:57,137 --> 00:18:58,669
     Well, maybe a little.

349
00:18:58,771 --> 00:19:00,939
 Has anypony tested it before?

350
00:19:01,341 --> 00:19:02,907
    Where's the fun in that?

351
00:19:07,547 --> 00:19:09,314
         There's MORE?

352
00:19:09,516 --> 00:19:11,949
     You're not thinking of
     backing out, are you?

353
00:19:12,051 --> 00:19:15,487
  No! I'm just thinking about
   drinking through straws.

354
00:19:16,089 --> 00:19:19,657
Are you the president
of my fan club, or not?

355
00:19:19,859 --> 00:19:21,209
    Of course, it's just...

356
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:23,160
   You wouldn't want to get
   impeached for dishonoring

357
00:19:23,263 --> 00:19:25,329
     my wishes, would you?

358
00:19:25,431 --> 00:19:27,465
      I-- Is that a thing?

359
00:19:29,802 --> 00:19:30,968
          Light it up!

360
00:19:35,074 --> 00:19:38,276
     OK, now I am thinking
    about backing out!

361
00:19:38,378 --> 00:19:39,443
                       Too late!

362
00:19:55,795 --> 00:19:58,362
  I know I was supposed to let
  you make your own decisions,

363
00:19:58,464 --> 00:20:00,598
   but that doesn't mean I
  can't swoop in and save you

364
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:01,866
       from time to time.

365
00:20:04,404 --> 00:20:06,170
        If I'd known you
        were gonna bail,

366
00:20:06,272 --> 00:20:08,173
       I would have done
       the trick myself!

367
00:20:08,975 --> 00:20:10,741
Great! So you won't
mind how that rope's

368
00:20:10,843 --> 00:20:12,110
about to coil around your hoof!

369
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:16,614
        Rivals for LIFE!

370
00:20:18,418 --> 00:20:20,518
Wouldn't have it any other way.

371
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:23,120
I'm sorry for joining
the Washouts...

372
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,490
Lightning Dust wasn't
who I thought she was.

373
00:20:25,692 --> 00:20:28,893
She didn't care about me being
scared or putting me in danger.

374
00:20:28,995 --> 00:20:32,296
She only wanted a good show,
even if it meant I got hurt.

375
00:20:32,398 --> 00:20:35,200
That's not the kind of
pony I wanna look up to.

376
00:20:35,902 --> 00:20:38,502
          I'm the one who should
          be apologizing...

377
00:20:38,604 --> 00:20:42,039
  for not acting like somepony
  who deserves a fan club.

378
00:20:42,141 --> 00:20:43,774
          I've been lucky enough
          to have somepony

379
00:20:43,876 --> 00:20:45,476
                  who thinks I'm
                  the coolest,

380
00:20:45,678 --> 00:20:47,912
      but there's nothing cool
      about making you feel like

381
00:20:48,014 --> 00:20:50,448
               you'll never be
               as awesome as me.

382
00:20:52,318 --> 00:20:54,885
        I think we should cancel
        the Washouts Fan Club,

383
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:58,990
 because I know a fan club that
 could use some new members.

384
00:20:59,392 --> 00:21:00,958
   The Rainbow Dash Fan Club!

385
00:21:05,531 --> 00:21:07,198
       Welcome to the
       first ever meeting

386
00:21:07,300 --> 00:21:10,134
     of the newest fan club
       for the awesomest,

387
00:21:10,236 --> 00:21:14,038
  previously under-appreciated
   pony in Ponyville...

388
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:15,740
    with founding member and
     president Rainbow Dash

389
00:21:15,842 --> 00:21:20,678
      presiding, it's the...
      Scootaloo Fan Club!

390
00:21:24,384 --> 00:21:26,484
       You know, Rainbow
        Dash was right.

391
00:21:26,586 --> 00:21:29,387
   Eavesdropping on your own
  fan club isn't weird at all.

